<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-08-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1520.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-08-22"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 22, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I enclose for your information a copy of a
                                correspondence<note n="†" xml:id="d314fn1">For enclosure see
                                correspondence with British legation, current series.</note> which
                            has taken place between her Majesty’s legation and this department upon
                            the subject of the withdrawal of the notice abrogating the agreement
                            contained in the convention of 1817, limiting the naval armament on the
                            lakes.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>